《'''2019年歐洲聯盟（脫離）（第2號）法令'''》（{{lang-en|''European Union (Withdrawal) (No. 2) Act 2019''}}，通稱「'''彭氏法令'''」），是由[[英国下议院|英國下議院]]議員[[彭浩禮|彭浩禮]]動議的一條[[國會法令|國會法令]]，法令要求[[英国首相|英国首相]]在某些情況下尋求押後[[英國脫歐|脫歐]]日期。如果下議院在2019年10月19日前未能通過[[英國脫歐協議|脫歐協議]]或{{tsl|en|No-deal Brexit|無協議脫歐}}的話，就會觸發本法令的主要條款。法令又提出將脫歐限期由2019年10月31日延遲至2020年1月31日，若獲得[[歐盟高峰會|歐盟高峰會]]接受的話，首相就有義務接受。

法令的部分條文詳列一旦歐盟高峰會提出其他脫歐限期的行動安排，要求英廷就英歐談判的進度定期提交報告，並載列首相致函歐洲理事會主席尋求延遲限期時的信件格式，以及剝奪首相拒絕修訂脫歐日的權力。法令在2019年9月9日獲[[御准|御准]]，同日生效。

[[鲍里斯·约翰逊|鲍里斯·约翰逊]]拜相後就有傳會考慮[[2019年英國休閉議會爭議|休會]]，反對派和[[後座議員|後座議員]]繼而在奪得國會議程控制權後動議及和議本法案。政府強烈反對法案，約翰遜本人和疑歐派議員多次稱此為「'''投降法令'''」。政府更曾被質疑審視不同選項，意圖令法令失去法律效力。10月19日，約翰遜依據本法令致函理事會主席[[唐納德·圖斯克|唐納德·圖斯克]]，正式請求押後脫歐日期<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ft.com/content/d9ec648a-f2bc-11e9-b018-3ef8794b17c6|work=Financial Times|date=2019-10-19|title=Boris Johnson asks for Brexit extension in three letters|last1=Khan|first1=Mehreen|last2=Parker|first2=George|access-date=2019-11-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191103064709/https://www.ft.com/content/d9ec648a-f2bc-11e9-b018-3ef8794b17c6|archive-date=2019-11-03|dead-url=no}}</ref>，同月28日獲正式批准<ref name=28Oct/>。10月30日，英國法律中的「離開日」相應地修訂為2020年1月31日晚上11時正<ref>The European Union (Withdrawal) Act 2018 (Exit Day) (Amendment) (No. 3) Regulations 2019 SI 2019 No. 1423, 30th October 2019.[http://www.legislation.gov.uk/uksi/2019/1423/regulation/2/made] {{Wayback|url=http://www.legislation.gov.uk/uksi/2019/1423/regulation/2/made |date=20191110011230 }}</ref>。

本法令在2020年1月23日被《{{tsl|en|European Union (Withdrawal Agreement) Act 2020|2020年歐洲聯盟（脫離協議）法令}}》廢除<ref name="repeal-provision">{{cite web |title=European Union (Withdrawal Agreement) Act 2020 |url=http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/2020/1/section/36/enacted |website=www.legislation.gov.uk |publisher=The National Archives |accessdate=2020-01-24 |archive-date=2022-04-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220429043443/https://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/2020/1/section/36/enacted }}</ref>。

== 背景 ==
2016年6月，[[英國去留歐盟公投|英國公投通過脫離歐洲聯盟]]<ref>{{cite news |title=EU Referendum: Results |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/politics/eu_referendum/results |work=[[英國廣播公司新聞|BBC News]] |access-date=2019-09-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191001030127/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/politics/eu_referendum/results |archive-date=2019-10-01 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。2017年2月，下議院以498票對114票通過《{{tsl|en|European Union (Notification of Withdrawal) Act 2017|2017年歐洲聯盟（通知脫離）法令}}》<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-38833883|title=Brexit: MPs overwhelmingly back Article 50 bill|last=|first=|date=2017-02-01|work=[[英國廣播公司新聞|BBC News]]|access-date=2019-10-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190527012644/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-38833883|archive-date=2019-05-27|dead-url=no}}</ref>。公投九個月後的2017年4月29日，當時在位的[[文翠珊|文翠珊]]政府{{tsl|en|United Kingdom invocation of Article 50 of the Treaty on European Union|英國引用里斯本條約第50條|正式引用里斯本條約第50條}}<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-39143978 |title=Brexit: Article 50 has been triggered - what now? |date=2017-03-29 |work=[[英國廣播公司新聞|BBC News]] |access-date=2019-10-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200103013048/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-39143978 |archive-date=2020-01-03 |dead-url=no }}</ref>，開展脫歐程序。[[2017年英國大選|2017年6月的大選]]，文翠珊領導的[[保守黨_(英國)|保守黨]]意外失去國會大多數，不過得到[[民主统一党_(北爱尔兰)|民主統一黨]]支持而能夠繼續執政<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/election-2017-40219030 |title=May to form 'government of certainty' with DUP backing |date=2017-06-09 |work=[[英國廣播公司新聞|BBC News]] |access-date=2019-10-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170610033637/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/election-2017-40219030 |archive-date=2017-06-10 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

2018年11月，{{tsl|en|Brexit withdrawal agreement|英國脫離歐洲聯盟協議}}對外公佈<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-46188790 |title=Brexit: UK and EU 'agree text' of draft withdrawal agreement |date=2018-11-14 |work=[[英國廣播公司新聞|BBC News]] |access-date=2019-10-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200103033332/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-46188790 |archive-date=2020-01-03 |dead-url=no }}</ref>，但{{tsl|en|Parliamentary votes on Brexit|英國脫歐國會表決|僅在2019年初就被三度否決}}<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.euronews.com/2019/03/28/mps-prepare-to-vote-on-a-new-brexit-motion-on-friday-but-few-are-clear-what-they-will-be-v |title=No-deal Brexit fears rise as MPs defeat May's deal for third time |location=Lyon |date=2019-03-28 |work=[[欧洲新闻台|Euronews]] |agency=[[路透社|Reuters]] |access-date=2019-10-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190914154211/https://www.euronews.com/2019/03/28/mps-prepare-to-vote-on-a-new-brexit-motion-on-friday-but-few-are-clear-what-they-will-be-v |archive-date=2019-09-14 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。英國國會亦通過《[[2019年歐洲聯盟（脫離）法令|2019年歐洲聯盟（脫離）法令]]》，不准{{tsl|en|No-deal Brexit|無協議脫歐|在無協議情況下脫歐}}，並要求延長第50條程序<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-47562995 |title=Brexit: MPs vote to reject no-deal Brexit |date=2019-03-14 |work=[[英國廣播公司新聞|BBC News]] |access-date=2019-10-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191017232332/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-47562995 |archive-date=2019-10-17 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-47557216 |title=Brexit Article 50: Tusk to ask EU to consider long extension |date=2019-03-14 |work=[[英國廣播公司新聞|BBC News]] |access-date=2019-10-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190914063639/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-47557216 |archive-date=2019-09-14 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。英國政府和歐洲理事會隨後同意押後原訂2019年3月29日的脫歐日期，先是2019年4月12日、繼而是2019年10月31日<ref>{{Cite web |last=Wright |first=Georgina |url=https://www.instituteforgovernment.org.uk/explainers/article-50-options |title=Article 50 extension |work=Explainers |date=2019-10-29 |publisher={{tsl|en|Institute for Government||Institute for Government}} |access-date=2019-10-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190702104047/https://www.instituteforgovernment.org.uk/explainers/article-50-options |archive-date=2019-07-02 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

推動脫歐不果的文翠珊遭受保守黨黨內反對，她最終在2019年6月7日辭任[[保守黨領袖_(英國)|保守黨黨魁]]，同年7月24日離任首相<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-48395905 |title=Theresa May quits: UK set for new PM by end of July |date=2019-09-04 |work=[[英國廣播公司新聞|BBC News]] |access-date=2019-10-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191130125642/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-48395905 |archive-date=2019-11-30 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。[[2019年英国保守党领袖选举|繼任]]黨魁和首相的約翰遜提出「不脫歐毋寧死」方針，強調無論有否協議，英國必須在10月31日離開歐盟<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.heraldscotland.com/news/17728774.boris-johnson-makes-do-or-die-commitment-on-brexit-by-oct-31-as-he-hits-campaign-trail/ |title=Boris Johnson makes 'do or die' commitment on Brexit by Oct 31 as he hits campaign trail |last=Settle |first=Michael |date=2019-06-25 |newspaper={{tsl|en|The Herald (Glasgow)||The Herald}} |publisher=Herald & Times Group |location=Glasgow |issn=0965-9439 |access-date=2019-10-29 |archive-date=2020-07-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200729092147/https://www.heraldscotland.com/news/17728774.boris-johnson-makes-do-or-die-commitment-on-brexit-by-oct-31-as-he-hits-campaign-trail/ }}</ref>。

8月28日，約翰遜建議女皇[[伊丽莎白二世|伊利沙伯二世]]下令國會自9月第二週起[[2019年英國休閉議會爭議|休閉]]至10月14日，意味復會之時僅距離歐盟峰會三日<ref name=":22">{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-49493632 |title=Parliament suspension: Queen approves PM's plan |date=2019-08-28 |work=[[英國廣播公司新聞|BBC News]] |access-date=2019-10-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190828151117/https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-49493632 |archive-date=2019-08-28 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。是次的會期中止令國會審議政府法案的時間大大縮短，被批評意圖繞過國會推動無協議脫歐。[[下議院議長_(英國)|下議院議長]][[约翰·伯科_(英国)|白高漢]]形容是次休會是「憲政暴行」，民眾斥責等同[[政變|政變]]或[[自我政变|自我政變]]<ref name=":22" />。

== 內容 ==
法令包含5則條款和一個附表，載有請求延長談判期的信件格式<ref name=the_Act>{{cite web |url= http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/2019/26 |title= European Union (Withdrawal) (No. 2) Act 2019 |work= legislation.gov.uk |publisher= HM Government |accessdate= 2019-09-29 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20190929042010/http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/2019/26 |archive-date= 2019-09-29 |dead-url= no }}</ref>。

* 引言：法令詳題及引言
* 第1條「有關聯合王國脫離歐洲聯盟的職責」：首相有義務為了脫歐協議談判而請求延長第50條談判期，除非下議院通過批准脫歐協議或批准無協議下脫歐的動議並得上議院辯論。若動議不獲批准，首相有義務請求延長至2019年10月19日。
* 第2條「報告聯合王國與歐洲聯盟關係的談判進度」：政府有義務在2019年11月30日發表談判的首份進度報告，若被否決或修訂則需要發表第二份報告，詳列未來談判的計劃；政府亦有義務自2020年2月7日起每四個星期發布進度報告，除非另有指示。
* 第3條「有關延長第五十條的職責」：首相有義務接受延長至2020年1月31日；首相亦獲准接受此新期限或請求下議院接受任何其他限期。
* 第4條「修訂現有條文」：修訂使法令不會與其他法律有衝突。
* 第5條「釋義、生效、範圍及簡稱」
* 附表「首相致函歐洲理事會主席之信件格式」：指明尋求延長期限的信件格式和字眼

==過程==
2019年9月3日，保守黨議員[[奥利弗·莱特温|奥利弗·莱特温]]動議容許下議院控制翌日一條有關脫歐的後座議員法案的二三讀、委員會和考慮修訂程序，最終以27票之差獲通過<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://metro.co.uk/2019/09/03/general-election-likely-mps-vote-seize-control-parliament-agenda-10679922/|title=General Election likely as MPs vote to seize control of Parliament agenda|last=Hockaday|first=James|date=2019-09-03|work={{tsl|en|Metro (British newspaper)||Metro}}|access-date=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190904215949/https://metro.co.uk/2019/09/03/general-election-likely-mps-vote-seize-control-parliament-agenda-10679922/|archive-date=2019-09-04|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite Hansard|title=European Union (Withdrawal)|speaker=|jurisdiction=Parliament of the United Kingdom|house=House of Commons|volume=664|column_start=132|column_end=136|url=https://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/2019-09-03/debates/C4B0BE00-2E57-4FA4-8958-CD6F37711635/EuropeanUnion(Withdrawal)|date=2019-09-03|accessdate=2019-09-10|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190904031334/https://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/2019-09-03/debates/C4B0BE00-2E57-4FA4-8958-CD6F37711635/EuropeanUnion(Withdrawal)|archivedate=2019-09-04|dead-url=no}} {{Wayback|url=https://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/2019-09-03/debates/C4B0BE00-2E57-4FA4-8958-CD6F37711635/EuropeanUnion(Withdrawal) |date=20190904031334 }}</ref>。21名保守黨議員因倒戈支持法案而被[[2019年英國保守黨開除黨籍風波|開除黨籍]]（包括{{tsl|en|Father of the House (United Kingdom)|下議院院父}}暨前[[財政大臣_(英國)|財政大臣]][[祁淦禮|祁淦禮]]、另外8名[[戴维·卡梅伦|卡梅倫]]和文翠珊任內閣員、前首相[[温斯顿·丘吉尔|邱吉爾]]的外孫[[尼古拉斯·索梅斯|尼古拉斯·索梅斯]]等<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.euronews.com/2019/09/03/no-to-no-deal-brexit-the-tory-rebels-defying-boris-johnson|title='No to no-deal Brexit': the 21 Tory rebels who defied Boris Johnson|last=Sandford|first=Alasdair|date=2019-09-04|work=Euronews|access-date=|last2=Crowcroft|first2=Orlando|ref=harv|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190903234945/https://www.euronews.com/2019/09/03/no-to-no-deal-brexit-the-tory-rebels-defying-boris-johnson|archive-date=2019-09-03|dead-url=no}}</ref>{{efn|21名被驅逐出黨的議員為：[[吉托·貝伯|吉托·貝伯]]、[[理查·貝尼昂|理查·貝尼昂]]、[[史蒂芬·布賴恩|史蒂芬·布賴恩]]、[[阿利斯特·伯特|阿利斯特·伯特]]、[[格雷格·克拉克|格雷格·克拉克]]、[[祁淦禮|祁淦禮]]、[[大衛·高克|大衛·高克]]、[[簡意寧|簡意寧]]、[[多米尼克·格里夫|多米尼克·格里夫]]、[[山姆·吉馬|山姆·吉馬]]、[[夏文達|夏文達]]、[[史提芬·哈蒙德|史提芬·哈蒙德]]、[[理查·哈靈頓|理查·哈靈頓]]、[[玛戈特·詹姆斯|玛戈特·詹姆斯]]、[[奥利弗·莱特温|奥利弗·莱特温]]、[[安妮·弥尔顿|安妮·弥尔顿]]、[[卡罗琳·诺克斯|卡罗琳·诺克斯]]、[[宋碧芝|宋碧芝]]、[[尼古拉斯·索梅斯|尼古拉斯·索梅斯]]|[[羅利·斯圖爾特|羅利·斯圖爾特]]、[[艾德·維濟|艾德·維濟]]}}），加上保守黨的[[菲利浦·李|菲利浦·李]]轉投[[自由民主党_(英国)|自民黨]]，令政府失去國會的有效多數。肅清過後，首相弟弟[[約·約翰遜|約·約翰遜]]和[[安珀·路德|安珀·路德]]決定辭職離開內閣，以示抗議<ref name="BBC2019">{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-49623737|title=Amber Rudd resigns from government|date=2019-09-07|work=BBC News|access-date=2019-09-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190908050056/https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-49623737|archive-date=2019-09-08|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/brothers-sacking-of-21-tory-rebels-was-the-final-straw-for-jo-johnson-qzcdzgmz0|title=Brother's sacking of 21 Tory rebels was final straw for Jo Johnson|last=Wright|first=Oliver|date=2019-09-06|work=The Times|last2=Zeffman|first2=Henry|last3=Elliot|first3=Francis|access-date=2019-09-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190927202849/https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/brothers-sacking-of-21-tory-rebels-was-the-final-straw-for-jo-johnson-qzcdzgmz0|archive-date=2019-09-27|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

9月4日，工黨議員彭浩禮動議《'''歐洲聯盟（脫離）（第6號）法案'''》。政府由始至終都鮮明反對，表明若獲下議院通過，首相將會馬上[[英國定期國會法|動議提前大選]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.itv.com/news/2019-09-04/brexit-emergency-debate-vote-boris-johnson-as-mps-bid-to-block-no-deal-brexit-after-wrestling-control-of-commons-agenda/|title=Prime Minister Boris Johnson moves for election after Bill to block no deal passes the Commons|last=|first=|date=2019-09-04|work=[[ITV新聞|ITV News]]|access-date=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190908063248/https://www.itv.com/news/2019-09-04/brexit-emergency-debate-vote-boris-johnson-as-mps-bid-to-block-no-deal-brexit-after-wrestling-control-of-commons-agenda/|archive-date=2019-09-08|dead-url=no}}</ref>。法案以329票對300票獲二讀<ref>{{Cite Hansard|title=European Union (Withdrawal) (No. 6) Bill: Second Reading|speaker=|jurisdiction=Parliament of the United Kingdom|house=House of Commons|volume=664|column_start=247|column_end=250|url=https://hansard.parliament.uk/commons/2019-09-04/debates/85267906-8A67-44A5-B31E-94C07B13FE1E/EuropeanUnion(Withdrawal)(No6)Bill|date=2019-09-04|accessdate=2019-09-10|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20191228230303/https://hansard.parliament.uk/commons/2019-09-04/debates/85267906-8A67-44A5-B31E-94C07B13FE1E/EuropeanUnion(Withdrawal)(No6)Bill|archivedate=2019-12-28|dead-url=no}} {{Wayback|url=https://hansard.parliament.uk/commons/2019-09-04/debates/85267906-8A67-44A5-B31E-94C07B13FE1E/EuropeanUnion(Withdrawal)(No6)Bill |date=20191228230303 }}</ref>，之後法案在委員會階段被修訂一次，就是[[斯蒂芬·金諾克|斯蒂芬·金諾克]]提出讓國會重新審議脫歐協議的修正案，最終因為沒有點票員負責「反對」而意外地獲得通過。法案同日獲三讀，比數為327票對299票<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-49580185|title=Brexit: MPs back bill aimed at blocking no deal|last=|first=|date=2019-09-04|work=BBC News|access-date=2019-09-08|language=en-GB|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190904191629/https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-49580185|archive-date=2019-09-04|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

法案同日呈交至上議院。由於上議院不如下議院般限制辯論發言的內容，有提議指政府會嘗試[[冗長辯論|拉布]]阻撓法案成法。不過影子上議院領袖{{tsl|en|Angela Smith, Baroness Smith of Basildon|巴兆敦的施安琪女男爵|施安琪女男爵}}動議[[辯論終結|剪布]]，要求在9月6日下午5點前完成審議程序，保守黨貴族繼而就剪布動議102項修正案，逼使上議院先處理其他法案<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.politicshome.com/news/uk/constitution/house-lords-reform/news/106286/tory-peers-launch-bid-block-no-deal-bill|title=Tory peers launch bid to block no-deal bill with filibuster in House of Lords|last=Tolhurst|first=Alain|date=2019-09-04|work={{tsl|en|PoliticsHome||PoliticsHome}}|access-date=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190904225826/https://www.politicshome.com/news/uk/constitution/house-lords-reform/news/106286/tory-peers-launch-bid-block-no-deal-bill|archive-date=2019-09-04|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/brexit-conservative-peers-block-no-deal-bill-hilary-benn-a9091391.html|title=Brexit: Conservative peers launch last-ditch effort to block no-deal bill|last=Woodcock|first=Andrew|date=2019-09-05|work=The Independent|access-date=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190904233105/https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/brexit-conservative-peers-block-no-deal-bill-hilary-benn-a9091391.html|archive-date=2019-09-04|dead-url=no}}</ref>。但到9月5日上午1點半，政府宣布結束拉布，容許法案若被修改的話則可在9月9日下議院會議上再次審議<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2019/sep/05/brexit-lords-agree-to-push-through-bill-preventing-no-deal-by-end-of-friday|title=Lords agree to push through bill preventing no-deal Brexit by end of Friday|last=Walker|first=Peter|date=2019-09-05|work=The Guardian|access-date=|last2=Murray|first2=Warren|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190908230353/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2019/sep/05/brexit-lords-agree-to-push-through-bill-preventing-no-deal-by-end-of-friday|archive-date=2019-09-08|dead-url=no}}</ref>。放棄拉布當日，上議院在無人反對下通過二讀<ref>{{Cite Hansard|title=European Union (Withdrawal) (No. 6) Bill|jurisdiction=Parliament of the United Kingdom|house=House of Lords|volume=799|column_start=1149|column_end=1231|url=https://hansard.parliament.uk/Lords/2019-09-05/debates/0AB50141-B0D1-4B6B-B9CA-92D27BD7E06C/EuropeanUnion(Withdrawal)(No6)Bill|date=2019-09-05|accessdate=2019-09-10|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190906180149/https://hansard.parliament.uk/lords/2019-09-05/debates/0AB50141-B0D1-4B6B-B9CA-92D27BD7E06C/EuropeanUnion(Withdrawal)(No6)Bill|archivedate=2019-09-06|dead-url=no}} {{Wayback|url=https://hansard.parliament.uk/Lords/2019-09-05/debates/0AB50141-B0D1-4B6B-B9CA-92D27BD7E06C/EuropeanUnion(Withdrawal)(No6)Bill |date=20190906180149 }}</ref>，翌日在無修訂下通過委員會、報告和三讀程序<ref>{{Cite Hansard|title=European Union (Withdrawal) (No. 6) Bill|speaker=|jurisdiction=Parliament of the United Kingdom|house=House of Lords|volume=664|column_start=1235|column_end=1278|url=|date=2019-09-06}}</ref>。9月9日，法案在會期中止前數小時獲得皇家御准，繼而成為法例<ref name=":1">{{Cite Hansard|title=Points of Order|jurisdiction=[[英国议会|Parliament of the United Kingdom]]|house=[[英国下议院|House of Commons]]|date=2019-09-09|volume=664|url=https://hansard.parliament.uk/commons/2019-09-09/debates/C1312A30-8ADB-4E20-9340-51722478F81A/PointsOfOrder|column=518|accessdate=2019-09-13|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190925222849/https://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/2019-09-09/debates/C1312A30-8ADB-4E20-9340-51722478F81A/PointsOfOrder|archivedate=2019-09-25|dead-url=no}} {{Wayback|url=https://hansard.parliament.uk/commons/2019-09-09/debates/C1312A30-8ADB-4E20-9340-51722478F81A/PointsOfOrder |date=20190925222849 }}</ref><ref name=":0">{{Cite Hansard|title=Royal Assent|jurisdiction=Parliament of the United Kingdom|house=[[英國上議院|House of Lords]]|date=2019-09-09|volume=799|url=https://hansard.parliament.uk/Lords/2019-09-09/debates/673DE0AD-F610-4C88-8B12-9CA778B46C59/RoyalAssent|column=1292}} {{Wayback|url=https://hansard.parliament.uk/Lords/2019-09-09/debates/673DE0AD-F610-4C88-8B12-9CA778B46C59/RoyalAssent |date=20211025204009 }}</ref>。

== 反應 ==
===政界===
法令在下議院通過當日，即9月4日，政府旋即動議[[英國定期國會法|定期國會法令]]、提前舉行大選，最後獲得298票贊成、56票反對，因未獲三分二超級多數（即434票）的支持而不獲通過。反對派相信政府意圖在提前大選而[[解散议会|國會被解散]]期間，確保英國能夠在無協議下脫歐，所以均投下反對票或棄權<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-49584907 |title=Boris Johnson's call for general election rejected by MPs |date=2019-09-04 |work=[[英國廣播公司新聞|BBC News]] |access-date=2019-10-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191029065051/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-49584907 |archive-date=2019-10-29 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。9月9日，政府第二次動議提前大選不果，僅獲293票贊成和46票反對<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-49630094 |title=Brexit: Boris Johnson's second attempt to trigger election fails |date=2019-09-10 |work=[[英國廣播公司新聞|BBC News]] |access-date=2019-10-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190915220706/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-49630094 |archive-date=2019-09-15 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

9月5日，約翰遜在[[韦克菲尔德|域飛]]警校記者會上，揚言寧願「死在溝渠」也不會請求延長談判<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.politicshome.com/news/uk/political-parties/conservative-party/boris-johnson/news/106326/boris-johnson-i-would-rather |title=Boris Johnson: I would rather be dead in a ditch than ask for an extension to Brexit |last=Schofield |first=Kevin |date=2019-09-05 |work={{tsl|en|PoliticsHome||PoliticsHome}} |publisher=[[Dod's_Parliamentary_Communications|Dod's Parliamentary Communications]] |access-date=2019-10-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190915115702/https://www.politicshome.com/news/uk/political-parties/conservative-party/boris-johnson/news/106326/boris-johnson-i-would-rather |archive-date=2019-09-15 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。{{tsl|en|Police Federation of England and Wales|英格蘭及威爾斯警察總會}}等組織批評約翰遜發表政治演說，影響警隊不偏不倚的形象。{{tsl|en|West Yorkshire Police|西約郡警察隊}}隊長莊·羅便翌日發聲明表示，演說原本計劃宣布新的治安政策，警方事前不知道首相會談及其他事務<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2019/sep/06/criticism-grows-boris-johnson-use-police-officers-political-speech |title=Police chief says force was not told about Boris Johnson speech plan |last=Weaver |first=Matthew |date=2019-09-06 |newspaper=[[衛報|The Guardian]] |publisher={{tsl|en|Guardian Media Group||Guardian Media Group}} |location=London |issn=1756-3224 |access-date=2019-10-29 |last2=Proctor |first2=Kate |last3=Walker |first3=Peter |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191107004519/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2019/sep/06/criticism-grows-boris-johnson-use-police-officers-political-speech |archive-date=2019-11-07 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。外界一直質疑約翰遜有否違法，[[司法大臣_(英國)|司法大臣]][[羅伯特·巴克蘭|羅伯特·巴克蘭]]在9月8日表示，他作為[[大法官_(英國)|大法官]]有義務維護[[法治|法治]]，亦已跟約翰遜討論法治的重要性，但否認傳聞會在首相犯法時就會請辭<ref>{{Cite news |last=Merrick |first=Rob |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/boris-johnson-news-latest-no-deal-brexit-law-robert-buckland-a9096646.html |title=Brexit: Boris Johnson must 'obey law', his own justice secretary reminds him in extraordinary warning |date=2019-09-08 |work=[[獨立報|The Independent]] |location=London |issn=0951-9467 |access-date=2019-10-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191107082131/https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/boris-johnson-news-latest-no-deal-brexit-law-robert-buckland-a9096646.html |archive-date=2019-11-07 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

9月9日，有報導指政府會按法令要求寫信請求延長談判期，但會同時致函宣判該請求無效，從而令法令失效。[[英国最高法院|最高法院]]前法官{{tsl|en|Jonathan Sumption, Lord Sumption|莊拿豐·沈順，沈順勳爵|沈順勳爵}}認為舉動或者觸犯[[藐視法庭|藐視法庭罪]]，內閣的[[官方律政專員|律政專員]]可能會集體請辭<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2019/sep/09/boris-johnson-sabotage-letter-to-eu-would-break-law |title=Boris Johnson 'sabotage' letter to EU 'would break law' |last=Mohdin |first=Aamna |date=2019-09-09 |newspaper=[[衛報|The Guardian]] |publisher={{tsl|en|Guardian Media Group||Guardian Media Group}} |issn=1756-3224 |location=London |access-date=2019-10-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191030023101/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2019/sep/09/boris-johnson-sabotage-letter-to-eu-would-break-law |archive-date=2019-10-30 |dead-url=no }}</ref>；前{{tsl|en|Director of Public Prosecutions (England and Wales)|刑事檢察處處長 (英格蘭及威爾斯)|刑事檢察處處長}}{{tsl|en|Ken Macdonald|健·麥當奴}}表示約翰遜或面臨被囚<ref>{{Cite news |last=White |first=Nadine |url=https://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/entry/boris-johnson-could-face-jaol_uk_5d740cdae4b07521022d5fce |title=Boris Johnson 'Could Face Prison' If He Refuses To Delay Brexit |date=2019-09-07 |work=[[赫芬顿邮报|HuffPost]] |publisher=[[威訊媒體|Verizon Media]] |access-date=2019-10-29 |archive-date=2022-04-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220404134743/https://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/entry/boris-johnson-could-face-jaol_uk_5d740cdae4b07521022d5fce }}</ref>；[[反對黨領袖_(英國)|反對黨領袖]][[傑瑞米·柯賓|傑瑞米·柯賓]]動議緊急辯論法治的重要性，期間政府依然強調政策乃不會押後脫歐期。動議在無反對下通過，被視為反對派的一大勝利<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.itv.com/news/2019-09-09/emergency-debates-ahead-of-vote-on-early-election/ |title=MPs demand publication of no-deal Brexit and prorogation documents |date=2019-09-09 |work=[[ITV新聞|ITV News]] |access-date=2019-10-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191028200407/https://www.itv.com/news/2019-09-09/emergency-debates-ahead-of-vote-on-early-election/ |archive-date=2019-10-28 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。[[YouGov|YouGov]]在9月6日至8日進行民調，結果顯示50%受訪者不同意政府違反法令，另有28%同意；脫歐派（52%－28%）和保守黨人（50%－34%）最為支持政府，而留歐派（8%－77%）、[[自由民主党_(英国)|自由民主黨]]（11%－76%）和[[工党_(英国)|工黨]]（14%－69%）則相反<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://yougov.co.uk/topics/politics/articles-reports/2019/09/09/52-leave-voters-want-boris-johnson-break-law-brexi |title=52% of Leave voters want Boris Johnson to break the law for Brexit |last=Smith |first=Matthew |date=2019-09-09 |website=[[YouGov|YouGov]] |access-date=2019-10-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191207115151/https://yougov.co.uk/topics/politics/articles-reports/2019/09/09/52-leave-voters-want-boris-johnson-break-law-brexi |archive-date=2019-12-07 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

同日，[[威爾斯黨|威爾斯黨]]下議院領袖{{tsl|en|Liz Saville Roberts|利絲·薩維·羅拔士}}宣布多黨派已開展討論，一旦約翰遜拒絕遵守法律，反對派將會開展{{tsl|en|Impeachment in the United Kingdom|英國彈劾程序|彈劾程序}}<ref name=":3">{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-wales-politics-49628435 |title=Brexit extension: 'Impeach Boris Johnson if law ignored' |date=2019-09-09 |work=[[英國廣播公司新聞|BBC News]] |access-date=2019-10-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190923095506/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-wales-politics-49628435 |archive-date=2019-09-23 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。彈劾程序久未動用，亦未曾有閣員和首相因而下台；迄今最後一位被彈劾的是1806年的{{tsl|en|Henry Dundas, 1st Viscount Melville|亨利·登打士，第一代美怡維子爵}}<ref name="cbf_impeachment">{{Cite journal|last=Caird|first=Jack Simpson|date=2016-06-06|title=Impeachment|url=https://researchbriefings.parliament.uk/ResearchBriefing/Summary/CBP-7612|journal=Commons Briefings|publisher=House of Commons Library|volume=7612|access-date=2019-09-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190924124951/https://researchbriefings.parliament.uk/ResearchBriefing/Summary/CBP-7612|archive-date=2019-09-24|dead-url=no}}</ref>。最近一次發動彈劾是在{{tsl|en|Parliamentary motion to impeach Tony Blair|彈劾貝理雅的國會動議|2004年}}，當年威爾斯黨有份領導國會嘗試令時任首相[[托尼·布莱尔|貝理雅]]為[[伊拉克战争|伊拉克戰爭]]作失實陳述而請辭<ref name=":3" />。當時是{{tsl|en|opposition frontbench|反對派前座議員}}的約翰遜也有明確支持彈劾動議，更在《[[每日电讯报|每日電訊報]]》撰文指控貝理雅「藐視國會和公眾」<ref name="price_prorogue">{{Cite news |url=https://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/entry/boris-johnson-impeach_uk_5d7ded82e4b00d69059a18b7 |title=How This Week Could See Parliament Impeach Boris Johnson Over Brexit |last=Price |first=Adam |author-link=Adam Price |date=2019-09-15 |access-date=2019-10-29 |work=[[赫芬顿邮报|HuffPost]] |publisher=[[威訊媒體|Verizon Media]] |archive-date=2022-04-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220403055210/https://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/entry/boris-johnson-impeach_uk_5d7ded82e4b00d69059a18b7 }}</ref>。

2019年9月26日，前首相[[约翰·梅杰|馬卓安]]在歐洲改革中心發表談話，擔心政府會引用《{{tsl|en|Civil Contingencies Act 2004|2004年民事應急法令}}》中容許政府在緊急情況下令法例失效的條文<ref name=":5" />，去動用[[樞密院令|樞密院令]]使法令失效至10月31日<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.politicshome.com/news/uk/political-parties/conservative-party/news/106861/sir-john-major-warns-boris-johnson-could |title=Sir John Major warns Boris Johnson could use 'political chicanery' to force through no-deal Brexit |last=Schofield |first=Kevin |date=2019-09-26 |work={{tsl|en|PoliticsHome||PoliticsHome}} |publisher=[[Dod's_Parliamentary_Communications|Dod's Parliamentary Communications]] |access-date=2019-10-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191102234204/https://www.politicshome.com/news/uk/political-parties/conservative-party/news/106861/sir-john-major-warns-boris-johnson-could |archive-date=2019-11-02 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。樞密院令與[[樞密令|樞密令]]有不同，前者可由[[英國樞密院|樞密院]]自行制定，後者則需要女皇的同意。樞密院令的制定因由通常都是技術原因，又或者規管醫療服務，不會使法規不適用<ref name=":5">{{Cite news |url=https://inews.co.uk/news/politics/order-council-privy-john-major-benn-act-no-deal-brexit-extension-637732 |title=What is an Order of Council? Privy Council loophole John Major fears could scupper Benn Act on no-deal Brexit |last=McDonald |first=Karl |date=2019-09-27 |newspaper=[[I_(報章)|The i]] |publisher={{tsl|en|JPIMedia||JPIMedia}} |location=London |access-date=2019-10-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191007175900/https://inews.co.uk/news/politics/order-council-privy-john-major-benn-act-no-deal-brexit-extension-637732 |archive-date=2019-10-07 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。翌日下午，[[唐寧街10號|首相府]]否認約翰遜會透過樞密院令繞過法令，但繼續強調政府會帶領英國如期10月31日脫歐<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2019/sep/27/benn-act-is-watertight-gauke-deems-majors-brexit-fears-misplaced |title=No 10 dismisses John Major's fears it could circumvent Benn Act |last=Stewart |first=Heather |last2=Weaver |first2=Matthew |date=2019-09-27 |newspaper=[[衛報|The Guardian]] |publisher={{tsl|en|Guardian Media Group||Guardian Media Group}} |location=London |issn=1756-3224 |access-date=2019-10-29 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191008115931/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2019/sep/27/benn-act-is-watertight-gauke-deems-majors-brexit-fears-misplaced |archive-date=2019-10-08 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

===法院===
2019年9月12日，{{tsl|en|Jo Maugham|祖利昂·蒙}} {{Postnom|QC|country=GBR}} 和[[苏格兰民族党|苏格兰民族党]]司法發言人{{tsl|en|Joanna Cherry|祖安娜·車麗}} {{Postnom|QC|MP|country=GBR}} 入稟{{Le|蘇格蘭高等民事法院|Court of Session}}，要求當國會未能通過脫歐協議時，首相需要致函尋求押後。二人希望蘇格蘭法院獨有的{{tsl|en|nobile officium|特別救濟權}}能夠在約翰遜拒絕履行法令時，由法院以首相名義致函。而他們已在此前成功挑戰約翰遜的休會決定，法院在9月11日裁定決定屬非法<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2019/sep/12/anti-brexiters-new-legal-challenge-scotland-to-force-article-50-extension |title=Anti-Brexiters file new legal challenge to force article 50 extension |last=Carrell |first=Severin |date=2019-09-12 |access-date=2019-10-29 |newspaper=[[衛報|The Guardian]] |issn=1756-3224 |publisher={{tsl|en|Guardian Media Group||Guardian Media Group}} |location=London |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191108053311/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2019/sep/12/anti-brexiters-new-legal-challenge-scotland-to-force-article-50-extension |archive-date=2019-11-08 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

9月24日，最高法院在{{tsl|en|R (Miller) v The Prime Minister and Cherry v Advocate General for Scotland|女皇（米勒）訴首相及車麗訴蘇格蘭檢察總長}}一案中裁定與會無效和非法，國會因而在翌日復會<ref>{{Cite Hansard |title=Speaker's Statement |jurisdiction=Parliament of the United Kingdom |house=House of Commons |date=2019-09-25 |volume=664 |url=https://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/2019-09-25/debates/E477D91B-BF03-4F14-947D-09C6C4B3A0DC/Speaker’SStatement |column=651 |speaker=[[约翰·伯科_(英国)|John Bercow]] |position=[[下議院議長_(英國)|Speaker of the House of Commons]] |access-date=2019-10-29 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20191223235500/https://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/2019-09-25/debates/E477D91B-BF03-4F14-947D-09C6C4B3A0DC/Speaker%E2%80%99SStatement |archivedate=2019-12-23 |dead-url=no }} {{Wayback|url=https://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/2019-09-25/debates/E477D91B-BF03-4F14-947D-09C6C4B3A0DC/Speaker%E2%80%99SStatement |date=20191223235500 }}</ref>。[[英格蘭及威爾斯律政司|律政司]][[喬弗利·科克斯|喬弗利·科克斯]]當日早上表示政府沒有不遵守法令，但政府認為法令涵蓋的法律義務仍然是條懸而未決的問題<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-49826524|title=Parliament suspension: Angry Commons exchanges as MPs return to work|date=2019-09-25|access-date=2019-10-29|work=BBC News|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191015152208/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-49826524|archive-date=2019-10-15|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

10月7日，蘇格蘭法院拒絕受理蒙氏和車麗的訴訟，{{tsl|en|Outer House|初審庭}}認為「沒有違反法定責任的合理憂慮」，法庭收到的聲言顯示政府會遵守法令，因此法院無需頒佈命令強制政府守法。10月9日，{{tsl|en|Inner House|複審庭}}決定會在10月21日頒下最終判決，即法令限期過後兩日<ref>{{Cite news |last=McCall |first=Chris |url=https://www.scotsman.com/news/politics/brexit-court-of-session-continues-legal-challenge-until-after-october-19-deadline-1-5020369 |title=Brexit: Court of Session continues legal challenge until after October 19 deadline |newspaper=[[苏格兰人报|The Scotsman]] |issn=0307-5850 |publisher={{tsl|en|JPIMedia||JPIMedia}} |location=Edinburgh |date=2019-10-09 |access-date=2019-10-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191009111834/https://www.scotsman.com/news/politics/brexit-court-of-session-continues-legal-challenge-until-after-october-19-deadline-1-5020369 |archive-date=2019-10-09 |dead-url=no }}</ref>。起訴的二人繼而請求法庭若裁定政府必須致函的話而對方拒絕的話，法院則應動用特別救濟權寫信<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-scotland-scotland-politics-49959167|title=Judge dismisses no-deal Brexit court move|website=BBC News|date=2019-10-07|accessdate=2019-10-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191007134128/https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-scotland-scotland-politics-49959167|archive-date=2019-10-07|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2019/oct/07/court-rejects-latest-request-to-force-pm-to-ask-for-brexit-extension|last=Carrell|first=Severin|title=Court rejects latest request to force PM to ask for Brexit extension|newspaper=[[衛報|The Guardian]]|date=2019-10-07|access-date=2019-10-07|issn=1756-3224|publisher={{tsl|en|Guardian Media Group||Guardian Media Group}}|location=London|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191007131007/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2019/oct/07/court-rejects-latest-request-to-force-pm-to-ask-for-brexit-extension|archive-date=2019-10-07|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

10月21日，複審庭復審蒙氏和車麗的訴訟。二人承認約翰遜滿足了法令的要求，但辯稱第二封信抵銷了第一封信。法庭又拒絕政府要求結束審議案件，認為案件應該繼續「直至清楚顯示（彭氏法令）的義務已全數履行」<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.heraldscotland.com/news/17982923.scottish-court-rejects-uk-government-bid-dismiss-brexit-legal-action/ |last=Grant |first=Alistair |title=Scottish court rejects UK Government bid to dismiss Brexit legal action |newspaper={{tsl|en|The Herald (Glasgow)||The Herald}} |publisher=Herald & Times Group |location=Glasgow |issn=0965-9439 |date=2019-10-21 |access-date=2019-10-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191022004321/https://www.heraldscotland.com/news/17982923.scottish-court-rejects-uk-government-bid-dismiss-brexit-legal-action/ |archive-date=2019-10-22 |dead-url=no }}</ref>，意味政府未能擺脫法院的壓力<ref>{{Cite web|title=Scottish court keeps alive pressure on Boris Johnson over Brexit delay|url=https://www.ft.com/content/7678c2f4-f3f7-11e9-b018-3ef8794b17c6|accessdate=|author=|date=2019-10-21|format=|publisher=金融時報|language=|archive-date=2020-03-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200320233144/https://www.ft.com/content/7678c2f4-f3f7-11e9-b018-3ef8794b17c6|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

===議會辯論===

[[迪斯伯里_(英國國會選區)|迪士巴利]]議員[[薛寶拉|薛寶拉]]批評首相在國會形容此法為「投降法令」的字眼是毫無必要的煽動，又稱反對派議員定時收到的死亡恐嚇都曾提及「投降法令」和指控他們「背叛」。薛氏認為首相應該注意言行。約翰遜回應時斥責她「[[詐騙集團|謊言]]」不斷，結果引起一片譁然、「可恥」聲此起彼落<ref name=":4">{{Cite news|url=https://www.yorkshirepost.co.uk/news/politics/boris-johnson-dismisses-as-humbug-yorkshire-mps-calls-for-calmer-language-after-jo-cox-s-death-1-10017108|title=Boris Johnson dismisses as 'humbug' Yorkshire MPs' calls for calmer language after Jo Cox's death|last=Scott|first=Geraldine|date=2019-09-25|work={{tsl|en|Yorkshire Post||Yorkshire Post}}|access-date=2019-09-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190927194442/https://www.yorkshirepost.co.uk/news/politics/boris-johnson-dismisses-as-humbug-yorkshire-mps-calls-for-calmer-language-after-jo-cox-s-death-1-10017108|archive-date=2019-09-27|dead-url=no}}</ref>。[[巴特利和斯彭_(英國國會選區)|柏利和詩濱]]議員{{tsl|en|Tracy Brabin|翠絲·布禮彬}}再呼籲首相慎言、做好榜樣避免議員再受襲擊，因為她的上任[[乔·考克斯|祖·葛絲]]就是在{{tsl|en|Murder of Jo Cox|祖·葛絲遇刺案|2016年6月被新納粹分子刺殺身亡}}<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/voices/boris-johnson-jo-cox-brexit-mps-vote-election-supreme-court-parliament-a9120671.html|title=Boris Johnson tells the MP for Batley and Spen: The best way to honour Jo Cox's memory is to get Brexit done|last=Peck|first=Tom|date=2019-09-25|work=The Independent|access-date=2019-09-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190926220849/https://www.independent.co.uk/voices/boris-johnson-jo-cox-brexit-mps-vote-election-supreme-court-parliament-a9120671.html|archive-date=2019-09-26|dead-url=no}}</ref>。約翰遜再次拒絕，甚至表示悼念亡者的最佳方法就是「完成脫歐」，激發議事廳內更多憤怒<ref name=":4" />。

== 結果 ==
10月19日的下議院特別會議上，議員審議經修訂的脫歐協議<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2019/oct/09/parliament-set-for-brexit-showdown-on-19-october|last=Murphy|first=Simon|title=Parliament set for Brexit showdown on 19 October|work=The Guardian|date=2019-10-09|accessdate=2019-10-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191013225148/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2019/oct/09/parliament-set-for-brexit-showdown-on-19-october|archive-date=2019-10-13|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-49984367|title=Brexit: Special sitting for MPs to decide UK's future|website=BBC News|date=2019-10-09|accessdate=2019-10-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191009081839/https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-49984367|archive-date=2019-10-09|dead-url=no}}</ref>。國會又以322對306票通過[[奥利弗·莱特温|利氏]]修正案，決定延遲審議協議直至通過實施協議的立法<ref>{{cite web|url=https://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/2019-10-19/debates/48144FF8-0E08-455A-8175-1EB64918D29E/EuropeanUnion(Withdrawal)Acts|title=European Union (Withdrawal) Acts|website=House of Commons Hansard<!--volume 666[sic],columns 648-652-->|date=2019-10-19|accessdate=2019-10-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191021102239/https://hansard.parliament.uk/Commons/2019-10-19/debates/48144FF8-0E08-455A-8175-1EB64918D29E/EuropeanUnion(Withdrawal)Acts|archive-date=2019-10-21|dead-url=no}}</ref>。修正案觸發了本法令，要求首相馬上寫信予歐洲理事會主席[[唐納德·圖斯克|唐納德·圖斯克]]，請求延長脫歐談判期至2020年1月31日<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2019/oct/19/mps-put-brakes-on-boris-johnsons-brexit-deal-with-rebel-letwin-amendment|last1=Stewart|first1=Heather|last2=Proctor|first2=Kate|title=MPs put brakes on Boris Johnson's Brexit deal with rebel amendment|newspaper=[[衛報|The Guardian]]|date=2019-10-19|access-date=2019-10-19|issn=1756-3224|publisher=[[衛報媒體集團|Guardian Media Group]]|location=London|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191019161837/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2019/oct/19/mps-put-brakes-on-boris-johnsons-brexit-deal-with-rebel-letwin-amendment|archive-date=2019-10-19|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Brexit: Johnson vows to press on despite defeat over deal delay|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-50110601|accessdate=2019-10-19|date=2019-10-19|work=[[英國廣播公司新聞|BBC News]]|dead-url=no|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191019201320/https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-50110601|archive-date=2019-10-19}}</ref>。首相最終寫了兩封信：第一封信乃依照本法令指明尋求延長，但首相沒有簽名；第二封信則強調自己認為押後脫歐會是一個錯誤，希望理事會主席和成員協助，確保英國如期脫離歐盟，而信件副本也給了其他成員國；上述信函由英國常駐歐盟代表發出，並且簽署附函確定第一封信是依照彭氏法令而撰<ref name="unsigned letter and cover note">Letters and note: [https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/letters-from-the-uk-to-the-eu-council-19-october-2019 unsigned letter and cover note] {{Wayback|url=https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/letters-from-the-uk-to-the-eu-council-19-october-2019 |date=20191021011753 }}; [https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/prime-ministers-letter-to-president-donald-tusk-19-october-2019 signed letter] {{Wayback|url=https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/prime-ministers-letter-to-president-donald-tusk-19-october-2019 |date=20191021011714 }}.</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Brexit: PM sends letter to Brussels seeking further delay|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-50112924|date=2019-10-19|dead-url=no|website=BBC News|access-date=2019-10-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191020012621/https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-50112924|archive-date=2019-10-20}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2019/oct/19/eu-will-grant-brexit-extension-if-johnson-sends-letter-says-brussels|last=Boffet|first=Daniel|title=Boris Johnson sends unsigned request to Brussels for Brexit delay|newspaper=[[衛報|The Guardian]]|date=2019-10-20|access-date=2019-10-20|issn=1756-3224|publisher={{tsl|en|Guardian Media Group||Guardian Media Group}}|location=London|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191019183529/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/2019/oct/19/eu-will-grant-brexit-extension-if-johnson-sends-letter-says-brussels|archive-date=2019-10-19|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

10月22日，實施脫歐協議的法案《歐洲聯盟（脫離協議）法案》在下議院以329票對299票獲二讀，但限制法案在三日內完成所有程序的「時限動議<ref>{{Cite web|title=英國脫歐真的到了「最後關頭」？|url=https://www.hk01.com/分析評論/389048/英國脫歐真的到了-最後關頭|accessdate=2020-08-01|date=2019-10-22|last=葉德豪|work=香港01|language=zh-HK}}</ref>」（或譯「程序動議<ref>{{Cite web|title=昨晚这半小时，英国与“有协议如期脱欧”无限接近|url=https://news.sina.cn/global/szzx/2019-10-23/detail-iicezzrr4274762.d.html|accessdate=2020-08-01|author=|date=2019-10-23|format=|work=news.sina.cn|publisher=|language=}}</ref>」）則以308對322票被否決，反對者認為動議將令國會沒有足夠時間檢視脫歐協議<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-50146182|title=Brexit bill 'in limbo' as MPs reject timetable|website=BBC News|date=2019-10-22|accessdate=2019-10-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191022185628/https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-politics-50146182|archive-date=2019-10-22|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/politics/blog/live/2019/oct/22/brexit-boris-johnson-deal-leave-eu-live-news|last=Rawlinson|first=Kevin|title=Brexit legislation 'paused' after MPs reject Boris Johnson's timetable|work=The Guardian|date=2019-10-22|accessdate=2019-10-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191022071202/https://www.theguardian.com/politics/blog/live/2019/oct/22/brexit-boris-johnson-deal-leave-eu-live-news|archive-date=2019-10-22|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

10月28日，歐盟正式通過押後脫歐限期<ref name="28Oct">{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-50205603|title=Brexit: Johnson agrees to Brexit extension - but urges election|publisher=BBC News|date=2019-10-28|accessdate=2019-11-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191103165815/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-50205603|archive-date=2019-11-03|dead-url=no}}</ref>。翌日，約翰遜的[[2019年英國大選|提前大選]][[2019年提前國會大選法令|動議]]獲國會通過<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-50229318|publisher=BBC News|date=2019-10-29|accessdate=2019-11-04|title=UK set for 12 December general election after MPs' vote|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191105122816/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-50229318|archive-date=2019-11-05|dead-url=no}}</ref>。保守黨最後奪得80席優勢，成為[[玛格丽特·撒切尔|戴卓爾夫人]]時期後最大勝選<ref>{{cite web|url=https://apnews.com/1ae2a55c4595a8e1757d1797c8c1c0d8|publisher=Associated Press|title=The Latest: UK's Conservatives end up with majority of 80|date=2019-12-13|access-date=2020-01-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191214130717/https://apnews.com/1ae2a55c4595a8e1757d1797c8c1c0d8|archive-date=2019-12-14|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

